# git-guard allowlist — one pattern per line, matched as substring of remote URL
# Lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# A remote URL is approved if it contains any pattern in this file.
# The check applies to: git commit, git push, git tag.
# If a repo has no remote 'origin', all write ops are blocked.
#
# Examples:
#   github.com/your-org      matches all repos in your org
#   your-company.com         matches any remote on your company's domain
#   github.com/yourname      matches your personal forks
